author: Hopkins
title: Burger King Brings Back Fan Favorite Item to New York State Locations - NewsBreak
text:
By Hopkins ,
17 minutes ago Fast food giant Burger King has announced that they're bringing back a fan favorite menu item December 19. The special will go on "as long as supplies last", at all New York state and nationwide restaurants, says the franchise. The New York Post describes the item, that has appeared sporadically over the past few years, as a "cult favorite". Read full article

author: Logan Ulrich
title: McVay: 'Obstacles' Blocking Rams Trade For Dolphins CB Jalen Ramsey
text:
The midpoint of June has passed in the calendar and the Dolphins still have CB Jalen Ramsey on the roster, despite signaling their clear intentions to trade him.
Rams HC Sean McVay , speaking at the team’s mandatory minicamp in Hawaii, said Los Angeles still has an interest in reuniting with Ramsey after trading him to Miami a couple of seasons ago. However, he pointed out there are some challenges to sort through.
“Usually, those are scenarios and situations that you have to have plans in place prior to executing some of the decisions that have occurred,” McVay said via NFL Media’s Kevin Patra . “Definitely don’t want to rule anything out because we’re always open-minded to onboarding and acquiring quality players and people like him if we’re able to do that, but there would be some obstacles that are real that are in the place of maybe preventing that from occurring.”
McVay elaborated a little more on what those obstacles consist of, per USA Today’s Cameron DaSilva .
“What is his salary? And are we able to take that on just based on our current situation when you onboard a player that’s earned the right to be paid where he’s at? Those are things that you’re usually planning months in advance and obviously, it was unforeseen that he would become available. And if you do execute a trade, what are they looking for in return? Is there a conversation to be had in terms of a portion of that contract that they pay? Are they interested in players or draft capital? So there’s a lot of layers to that.”
What it all seems to build down to, per McVay, is the Rams being hesitant about picking up the full tab on Ramsey’s salary for this year, which is over $20 million in guarantees. That’s a steep bill in addition to giving up a draft pick, and the Rams have been mindful of their spending with a battalion of young players due for big-money contract extensions over the next few years.
The Dolphins are still expected to trade Ramsey in the coming weeks but there is a lot to sort through with interested teams regarding how much of Ramsey’s salary they’ll pick up. The Rams remain a team to watch .
Ramsey, 30, is a former first-round pick of the Jaguars back in 2016. He signed a four-year, $23.35 million contract and was set to make a base salary of $3.63 million in 2019.
The Jaguars picked up Ramsey’s fifth-year option that cost them around $13 million for the 2020 season before trading him to the Rams for two first-round picks and a fourth-round selection.
He signed a five-year, $105 million extension before the start of the 2020 season, before he was traded to the Dolphins, later signing a three-year, $72.3 million deal with the team in 2024.
In 2024, Ramsey appeared in and started all 17 games for the Dolphins and recorded 60 tackles, two interceptions, one sack, and defended 11 passes.
We will have more on Ramsey as the news becomes available.

author: 聯合新聞網
title: iPhone 17系列傳全面漲價！定價遭外洩 iPhone 17 Pro還少1個儲存空間選項
text:
蘋果（Apple）將在9月發表全新手機iPhone 17系列，外界預期，旗艦款iPhone 17 Pro將會調漲定價
，並且取消一個儲存空間
選項。
iPhone 17系列將推出iPhone 17、iPhone 17 Air
、iPhone 17 Pro及iPhone 17 Pro Max
。據9to5mac報導，據微博爆料，iPhone 17 Pro將看齊iPhone 17 Pro Max，改成從256GB起跳開賣
，售價
為1049美元（約台幣3萬1414元），也意味著將完全取消原本的128GB選項，未來購買iPhone 17 Pro只能挑選256GB、512GB或1TB等儲存空間。
而iPhone 17 Pro起跳價1049美元也比iPhone 16 Pro 的 128GB、999 美元起（約台幣2萬9917元起）的定價有所提升。
蘋果先前採取過類似策略。2023 年，蘋果將iPhone 15 Pro Max的定價從1099 美元提高至1,199美元起（約台幣3萬5906元起），同時將256GB當成新的入門儲存容量，並稱「一開始就提供更多儲存空間」當成漲價的理由，如今iPhone 17 Pro也要走相同路線。
據爆料者稱，iPhone 17 Pro系列將整體漲價50美元（約台幣1497元），iPhone 17 Pro和iPhone 17 Pro Max入門儲存空間將以256GB起跳，而平價版iPhone 17及全新超薄手機iPhone 17 Air則可能維持128GB起跳。
據猜測，iPhone 17定價為799美元起（約台幣2萬3928元起）、iPhone 17 Air 取代Plus，定價為949美元起（約台幣28420元起）；iPhone 17 Pro為1049美元起（約台幣3萬1414元起），iPhone 17 Pro Max為1249 美元起（約台幣3萬7404元起）。

title: Actiu presenta sus tres muebles sostenibles esenciales para tu terraza este verano
text:
Actiu presenta sus tres muebles sostenibles esenciales para tu terraza este verano
Con la llegada del verano,
Actiu ha lanzado una colección de muebles ideales para poner a punto cualquier terraza. Estas piezas no destacan únicamente por su diseño y funcionalidad, sino también por su compromiso con la sostenibilidad. Concretamente, la colección incluye la mesa 'Dorik', la silla 'Fluit' y la butaca 'Meetia', cada uno con características únicas que los hacen imprescindibles para este verano.
Dorik: versatilidad y elegancia clásica
La mesa alta 'Dorik' es una opción versátil y cómoda, perfecta para terrazas de cualquier tamaño. La inspiración que llevó a la firma crear este diseño provino de las columnas dóricas de la antigua Grecia, algo que podemos intuir por el nombre del producto. En este sentido, 'Dorik' combina la elegancia atemporal con un diseño sencillo y limpio. Asimismo, cada mesa está fabricada con gran atención al detalle mediante moldeo rotacional, y puede expandirse utilizando múltiples columnas para crear mesas de reuniones. Sin duda alguna, este mueble es un claro ejemplo de cómo la arquitectura clásica puede fusionarse con el diseño funcional moderno, aportando un resultado original, único y vanguardista,
La inspiración de la mesa 'Dorik' proviene de la armonía y majestuosidad de la arquitectura griega.
Fluit: sostenibilidad y diseño premiado
Para complementar a la mesa 'Dorik', la silla 'Fluit' es la opción perfecta. Ha sido diseñada por el estudio Archirivolto Design, y reconocida con dos German Design Awards que ponen de relieve la excelencia en el diseño del producto. Por otro lado, esta pieza de mobiliario está hecha íntegramente de materiales reciclados: el 80% proviene de plástico reciclado postconsumo del sector agroalimentario y el 20% restante es fibra de vidrio reciclada. Este proceso de fabricación tan sostenible ha integrado también la tecnología de inyección de gas, lo que aporta a 'Fluit' un acabado delicado y suave al tacto. Además, esta colección de sillas sigue la filosofía de producción local de
Actiu, basándose en el concepto de Km 0.
La silla 'Fluit' de Actiu ha sido reconocida con dos German Design Awards.
Meetia: innovación y sostenibilidad en diseño
Por último,
Actiu ha seleccionado entre los muebles imprescindibles para terrazas a 'Meetia', la opción perfecta para aquellos que buscan optimizar el espacio de su terraza. Esta colección de butacas, diseñada por Ramón Esteve, combina diseño, funcionalidad y sostenibilidad en un mismo producto. Adicionalmente, estos muebles cuentan con un exterior de efecto roble o tela, y un interior tapizado con telas sostenibles, proporcionando un confort excepcional. La compañía y Ramón Esteve han logrado crear un diálogo entre el diseño y la sociedad, explorando nuevas formas de interacción con el entorno. El modelo refleja este compromiso, ofreciendo soluciones versátiles y sostenibles para los desafíos del mundo moderno.
La butaca 'Meetia' materializa la elegancia del estilo industrial.
Una terraza sostenible y elegante
En definitiva,
Actiu ha logrado combinar la sostenibilidad con el diseño de alta calidad en su nueva colección de muebles para terraza. Es por ello, que 'Dorik', 'Fluit' y 'Meetia' no solo mejoran la estética y funcionalidad de cualquier espacio exterior, sino que también contribuyen a un futuro más sostenible. Con estas opciones, la firma demuestra una vez más su compromiso con la innovación y la responsabilidad ambiental, ofreciendo muebles que son tanto agradables visualmente como respetuosos con el medio ambiente.

author: Jake Trotter
title: Short-handed Browns lose WRs Cooper, Moore to injury vs. Jets
text: CLEVELAND -- Leading [Browns](/nfl/team/_/name/cle/cleveland-browns) receiver [Amari Cooper](https://www.espn.com/nfl/player/_/id/2976499/amari-cooper) sat out Thursday night's [37-20](/nfl/game/_/gameId/401547623) playoff-clinching win over the [New York Jets](/nfl/team/_/name/nyj/new-york-jets) because of a heel injury. Cooper had been dealing with the injury all week. He tried to run during pregame warmups but was ultimately ruled inactive. The Browns lost another starting receiver to injury during the game. [Elijah Moore](https://www.espn.com/nfl/player/_/id/4372414/elijah-moore) left in the second quarter with a head injury. He caught an 8-yard touchdown from quarterback [Joe Flacco](https://www.espn.com/nfl/player/_/id/11252/joe-flacco) earlier in the quarter. In Sunday's win over the [Houston Texans](/nfl/team/_/name/hou/houston-texans), Cooper broke the Browns receiving record with 265 yards. He also had two touchdowns. Cooper is sixth in the NFL with 1,250 yards receiving despite playing with four different quarterbacks. He also has 72 receptions and five touchdowns. Cleveland (11-5) clinched a berth in the AFC playoffs for the third time since returning to the NFL in 1999.
